@sickjew I don‚Äôt think that was the goal. The goal was getting more attention on rape allegations against Cosby, and that succeeded, no?
RT @sickjew: @mrejfox Journalism isn't about being "overly kind" as a quid pro quo for access. It's about challenging people in power and r‚Ä¶
@sickjew I don‚Äôt think kindness was for access- it was for leaving Cosby no possible out for silence. Otherwise he‚Äôd claim ‚Äúattack/ambush‚Äù
@sickjew I have seen so many articles about Cosby‚Äôs silence regarding the rape allegations based on that interview, seems like more know now
@sickjew Cosby not responding to multiple public allegations of drugging/raping women, despite 3 overly kind attempts, extremely damning
@sickjew that is a perspective I hadn‚Äôt considered. I think asking the question at all in an unrelated interview is braver than 99% of media
@sickjew I think if he hadn‚Äôt asked in most possible inviting way, Cosby‚Äôs silence would not be so damning. He has no excuse with 3 chances.
@sickjew thank you for positive discussion. I agree with you. I disagree with criticizing that particular interview for it.
@sickjew I agree we shouldn‚Äôt shy away from explaining the charges elsewhere. I disagree that Simon should have brought it up in question
@sickjew I read the article both times you posted it. If you want to engage me, let‚Äôs have a productive discussion. I am not your enemy.
@sickjew Imho a lot of people became aware of the issue after the Hannibal Burress bit went viral, I don‚Äôt think it was a hidden issue

@sickjew about the ‚Äúallegations made in recent days‚Äù I really dont understand the insistence on pretending we all don‚Äôt know what that means
@sickjew Cosby backing down from the politest, calmer, most inviting way to ask that is much more telling than if he had asked explicitly
@sickjew he could have said ‚Äúno I didn‚Äôt do it‚Äù or ‚ÄúI am sorry to those involved‚Äù and Simon was as understanding and inviting as possible
@sickjew I really don‚Äôt get the criticism. All the people involved knew what he was talking about. If he had answered, would have been clear
@sickjew You are arguing with me like I am a troll- we agree on 99% of things. Complaining about that interview is not one of them.
@sickjew I know you are not serious. You, me, Simon, Cosby, everyone else with access to Twitter and the Internet knows what charges.
@sickjew The question would be ‚ÄúDo you have any response to those charges‚Äù if we want to continue to be pedantic
@sickjew I‚Äôm sorry but do you want to pretend that you, me, Simon, and Cosby all don‚Äôt understand what ‚Äúthese allegations‚Äù means?
@sickjew Scott Simon phrased the question perfectly to not give Cosby excuse of being ‚Äúattacked‚Äù- he very carefully invited him to talk
